<p class="eyebrow">Getting started</p>
<h1 class="mt-2 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Self-host with Docker.</h1>
<p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">Authly is pure self-host: pull the source, set a few environment variables, and run. <strong>No cloud account, no licence key, no phone-home</strong> — it runs fully offline and your data never leaves your database.</p>

<div class="mt-4 card card-body !py-3 flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-l-primary text-sm">
    <i data-lucide="hand-helping" class="size-4 text-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0"></i>
    <div>Prefer the step-by-step page with OS-specific Docker install tabs? See <a class="text-primary hover:underline" href="/self-host">the Self-Host guide</a>. This page is the condensed reference.</div>
</div>

<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">Prerequisites</h2>
<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Only <strong>Docker</strong> (Engine 24+ or Docker Desktop). PostgreSQL 16 and Redis 7 ship inside the Compose stack.</p>

<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">Quick start (local)</h2>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>git clone @(Authly.Web.SiteInfo.GitHubUrl).git
cd authly
docker compose up --build -d
docker compose logs -f app        <span class="tok-com"># watch migrations + super-admin seed</span></code></div>
<p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">Then open <code class="text-primary">http://localhost:8080</code>. EF Core migrations apply automatically on first boot.</p>

<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Environment variables</h2>
<div class="card overflow-hidden">
    <div class="overflow-x-auto scroll-thin">
        <table class="table">
            <thead><tr><th>Variable</th><th>Required</th><th>What it is</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>ENCRYPTION_KEY</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-danger">Required</span></td><td>32-byte base64 key (AES-256-GCM). Generate: <code>openssl rand -base64 32</code>.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>SUPERADMIN_EMAIL</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-danger">Required</span></td><td>First operator, seeded on boot.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>SUPERADMIN_PASSWORD</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-danger">Required</span></td><td>Forced change on first login.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>DATABASE_URL</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-neutral">Default</span></td><td>Postgres connection string (bundled service by default).</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>REDIS_URL</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-neutral">Default</span></td><td>Redis host:port (bundled service by default).</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>POSTGRES_PASSWORD</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-neutral">Default</span></td><td>Bundled Postgres password — override in production.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>RETENTION_AUDIT_DAYS</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-info">Optional</span></td><td>Audit-log retention (default 365).</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>RETENTION_LOGIN_HISTORY_DAYS</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-info">Optional</span></td><td>Login-history retention (default 90).</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT</code></td><td><span class="badge badge-info">Optional</span></td><td>OpenTelemetry collector endpoint.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
</div>

<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">Production</h2>
<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Put your required vars in a <code>.env</code> next to the overlay file and run the production stack behind a TLS reverse proxy:</p>
<div class="mt-3 code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>docker compose -f docker-compose.self-host.yml up -d</code></div>

<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">Observability (optional)</h2>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.observability.yml up -d
<span class="tok-com"># Grafana :3000 · Prometheus :9090 · Loki :3100 · OTLP :4317/4318</span></code></div>
<p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">Enable exporting under <strong>Admin → Observability</strong> (OTLP or Azure Monitor). Opt-in — nothing is exported until configured; changes apply on restart.</p>

<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">Stop &amp; clean up</h2>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>docker compose down            <span class="tok-com"># keep data</span>
docker compose down -v         <span class="tok-com"># wipe the pgdata volume</span></code></div>

